# Peaky Ledger ‚Äî Cursor Rules

## Project Overview

Peaky Ledger is a full-stack trading journal built with Next.js 16 (App Router), React 19, Supabase, Zustand, and vanilla CSS. See `CODEBASE.md` for exhaustive details.

## Tech Stack

- Next.js 16.2.7 (App Router) ‚Äî ‚öÝÔ∏è BREAKING CHANGES from older versions. Check `node_modules/next/dist/docs/`.
- React 19.2.4
- TypeScript 5 (strict mode)
- Supabase (Postgres + Auth + Storage with Row Level Security)
- Zustand 5 with persist middleware
- Recharts 3, TipTap 3, PapaParse 5, date-fns 4, Lucide React
- Vanilla CSS with HSL design tokens ‚Äî **NO TAILWIND**

## File Structure Rules

- `src/proxy.ts` ‚Äî middleware entry point (NOT `middleware.ts` in root)
- `src/app/(journal)/` ‚Äî route group containing all protected pages
- `src/utils/supabase/queries.ts` ‚Äî centralized database operations
- `src/utils/broker/adapter.ts` ‚Äî broker adapter interface pattern
- `src/types/journal.ts` ‚Äî ALL TypeScript interfaces and types
- `src/store/useJournalStore.ts` ‚Äî single Zustand store
- `src/app/globals.css` ‚Äî ALL CSS (design tokens, themes, component classes)
- Path alias: `@/*` ‚Üí `./src/*`

## Coding Conventions

- All page components use `'use client'` directive
- All database queries go through `queries.ts` (uses browser Supabase client)
- Server API routes use the server Supabase client from `server.ts`
- UI components use `React.forwardRef` pattern
- Modal component uses native `<dialog>` element
- Named exports for components, default exports for pages
- Inline styles are acceptable and common in this codebase
- CSS custom properties for all colors/shadows/transitions (never hardcode)

## Absolutely Do NOT

- Use Tailwind CSS or any CSS framework
- Create CSS module files
- Put Supabase queries directly in components
- Use `getServerSideProps` or `getStaticProps`
- Import `@supabase/supabase-js` directly ‚Äî use `client.ts` or `server.ts` wrappers
- Create new middleware files ‚Äî use `proxy.ts`
- Hardcode color values ‚Äî use CSS custom properties from globals.css

## Key Patterns

### Adding a new database entity:
1. Add table to `supabase/schema.sql` with RLS policy
2. Add TypeScript interface to `src/types/journal.ts`
3. Add CRUD functions to `src/utils/supabase/queries.ts`
4. Create the page/component that uses the new queries

### Adding a new broker:
1. Implement `BrokerAdapter` interface in `src/utils/broker/`
2. Add broker type to `BrokerType` union in `types/journal.ts`
3. Create API routes under `src/app/api/broker/`

### Environment Variables:
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL` / `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` (public)
- `FYERS_APP_ID` / `FYERS_APP_SECRET` / `FYERS_REDIRECT_URI` (server-only)
- `BROKER_TOKEN_ENCRYPTION_KEY` (server-only, 64 hex chars)

## Reference Files

- `CODEBASE.md` ‚Äî Complete project context and architecture
- `AGENTS.md` ‚Äî Agent behavioral rules
- `docs/architecture.md` ‚Äî System design and ER diagram
- `supabase/schema.sql` ‚Äî Database schema, triggers, RLS policies
